g.text: PC13 may interfere with RTC LSE and is left unconnected
The solder bridge can be broken and a diode placed instead.
This will allow driving WS2813B v1 and v2. Supply for LEDs on PCB will be 3.8-4.5V.
Logic high input should be 0.7*VDD to drive the old versions, so this will work w/ 3V3 logic.
